  "body": "I'm trying to write tests with the truffle-decoder, but it seems that it assumes it's a string:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/next/packages/truffle-decoder/lib/interface/contract-decoder.ts#L121\r\n\r\nThis means that I can't pass it the Ganache Provider object that I created in memory for my tests. Is there a way around this? Should the API always expect a string? Perhaps an inversion of control here would be good, and allow users to pass in a provider object instead.",
